cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DL 

The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with morphological segmentation for polysynthetic languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes novel multi-task training approaches and data augmentation methods, which are related to machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also uses neural sequence-to-sequence models, which are a type of neural network, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper explores cross-lingual transfer, which is related to transfer learning, making cs.DL (Deep Learning) a possible category as well.
